{
  "texts": [
    "While the content of the text might still be the same as the physical object, clouding the understanding as to why a different way of citing is needed, the digital form is not.",
    "This could have consequences for research focusing on materiality, as specific information (e.g.",
    "watermarks) can only be seen in the physical version and supported by specific infrastructure, and cannot be seen at all or can only be seen in a sub-optimal or skewed way in the digitised version.",
    "Nevertheless, the obvious pros of a digital version need to be brought forward, and enrichment of the data (e.g.",
    "in the form of Linked Open Data) can only be provided in a datafied version and not adequately in the physical object."
  ]
}